<!-- 
  SITEMAP SUBMISSION GUIDE
  =========================
  
  ## How to Submit to Google Search Console:
  1. Go to https://search.google.com/search-console/
  2. Verify your domain ownership if not already done
  3. Navigate to "Sitemaps" in the left sidebar
  4. Enter your sitemap URL: https://www.altaftoolshub.app/sitemap.xml
  5. Click "Submit" - Google will automatically crawl and index your pages
  6. Monitor the "Coverage" report to track indexing status
  
  ## How to Submit to Bing Webmaster Tools:
  1. Go to https://www.bing.com/webmasters/
  2. Sign in and add your site if not already added
  3. Navigate to "Sitemaps" in the left menu
  4. Click "Submit sitemap"
  5. Enter: https://www.altaftoolshub.app/sitemap.xml
  6. Bing will automatically fetch and process your sitemap
  
  ## Best Practices for Sitemap Management:
  - Update lastmod dates when pages change significantly
  - Keep sitemap under 50MB and 50,000 URLs (we're well within limits)
  - Use priority to indicate relative importance (1.0 = highest)
  - Set changefreq realistically:
    * daily: Homepage with frequent updates
    * weekly: Active tools and blog pages
    * monthly: Static pages like terms, privacy, documentation
  - Include image metadata for better image search visibility
  - Add mobile:mobile tag for mobile-friendly pages
  - Validate sitemap at https://www.xml-sitemaps.com/validate-xml-sitemap.html
  - Submit sitemap URL in robots.txt: Sitemap: https://www.altaftoolshub.app/sitemap.xml
  - Monitor Google Search Console for crawl errors
  - Update sitemap when adding new pages or removing old ones
  
  ## Priority Guidelines:
  - 1.0: Homepage
  - 0.9-0.95: Primary tools and important pages
  - 0.8-0.85: Secondary tools
  - 0.7: Resource pages (blog, FAQ, documentation)
  - 0.6: Legal pages (terms, privacy)
-->
